* Vagrant environment

Provided vagrantfile assumes you are using vmware provider, make necessary changes if using something else. To try out the environment, start up virtual machine with command:

vagrant up

Now transfer magento 2.1 (with sample data) install file to server. Currently the file is called "Magento-CE-2.1.7_sample_data-2017-05-30-09-30-10.tar.bz2". vagrant-scp plugin makes this easy for you.

After the transfer is complete, ssh to the machine, unpack magento file and run cli installer:

vagrant ssh
cd /services/magento
tar xf ~/Magento-CE-2.1.7_sample_data-2017-05-30-09-30-10.tar.bz2
php bin/magento setup:install --admin-firstname=vagrant --admin-lastname=vagrant --admin-user=admin --admin-password=pass1234 --admin-email="changeme@mailinator.com" --backend-frontname="admin_abc1"

Once installation is completed, you should be able to access admin via url:

http://localhost:3080/admin_abc1

and frontend via url:

http://localhost:3080/

If you want to start development server for frontend, use:

npm start

Note: npm start will fail, if you have installed node modules outside vagrant environment and vice versa. That's why we remove node_modules folder on init.
